{"title":"2. Geriatría. Demografía y políticas publicas","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Geriatría/2. Geriatría. Demografía y políticas publicas-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Demografía\\NGRS 11","guid":"_aO7EDkas9Ymb19dCwEjNQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Puntos Clave:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"1. Incremento de\\Npoblación mayor:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• ↑ n° y proporción de adultos mayores globalmente.","guid":"TCfcgph_0lSJPd8sHSF95Q","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• Causas: ↑ esperanza de vida, ↓ fertilidad y ↓ mortalidad.","guid":"LkzNuhoJLIBBwDNERjZLZw","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"2. Regiones menos desarrolladas:","guid":"qF_6ZhP8usg4w6x2qvcdDg","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• ↑ tasa de envejecimiento poblacional futuro.","guid":"SFmW9qDQmhTfLjDMC-wPuQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"3. Enfermedades crónicas no\\Ntransmisibles (ECNT):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• ↑ prevalencia en adultos mayores.","guid":"oZ08qqpEHPBDLl1mzSQxWA","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• ↑ carga financiera comparado con enfermedades transmisibles.","guid":"hCrto8NUAVGEGvPYN1NDoA","children":[]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"1","text":"4. EE.UU. y\\Ngeneración Baby\\NBoomer:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• ↑ n° adultos mayores.","guid":"hA4SSdf3pRy9dGFIwg3cPw","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"• ↑ proporción de adultos mayores de minorías raciales y étnicas.","guid":"5ur-yK38KCbenrHk0j6O3g","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"1","text":"5. Desigualdades\\Nen EE.UU.:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• Desigualdades en ingresos y pobreza en adultos mayores según sexo, raza/origen étnico y si viven solos.","guid":"bmu9veeL0zTkC0nmZPGNuw","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"1","text":"6. Dependencia de\\Nprogramas públicos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"16","parent":"15","text":"• Adultos mayores en EE.UU. dependen de Medicare y Seguridad Social.","guid":"FufW9Pn-V34gB3krDpn8Rg","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"15","text":"• Gasto en salud mayor comparado con adultos jóvenes.","guid":"mqx5Pwo2XmazaPuXbhr0Yw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"0","text":"Tendencias Globales de\\NEnvejecimiento y Demografía","guid":"vpJAqpWPZewXbMD29DTAew","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"1. Declive global en fertilidad y\\Nmortalidad (UN, 2019):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"20","parent":"19","text":"• ↑ esperanza de vida → Era de envejecimiento poblacional.","guid":"Cxflr7sAWyZ7DwvuyyVvfg","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"19","text":"• Definición: Cambio en la composición etaria hacia ≥65 años.","guid":"CgTkQ56b-uUs-0WMpriffQ","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"19","text":"• Variedad geográfica en el envejecimiento.","guid":"Yg7Amh8AVXnJlTp37eYOnw","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"18","text":"2. Proporción de adultos\\N≥65 años (2020):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"• Mundo: 9.3%.","guid":"ajIdWCJcb_xOvsM6zhfNkw","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"• Sub-Sahariana: 3.0%.","guid":"CBQWH3NhRzk2aXKcPErBKQ","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"• Oceanía (exc. Aus. y NZ): 4.2%.","guid":"vNO-BxkSypdaOeAgZAAXrQ","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"• Norte de África y Asia Occidental: 5.8%.","guid":"_PGUZc7_2Vrbtr0J6Jev8w","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"• Asia Central y Meridional: 6.1%.","guid":"GwwZNRm7fwflmmXXXR0ICw","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"23","text":"• América Latina y Caribe: 9.0%.","guid":"WVadLfH5-F84l_Sufpg9hg","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"23","text":"• Asia Oriental y Sudoriental: 11.6%.","guid":"ftSMrifok-t-Eaxq55dHIw","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"23","text":"• Australia y NZ: 16.2%.","guid":"l2Yq0q7QvgE35eK4rv6T6g","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"23","text":"• Europa y Norteamérica: 18. 3%.","guid":"WahQX44VseA5lYu027_f9Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"18","text":"3. Envejecimiento\\Nregional:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• África Sub-Sahariana: ↓ proporción (1950-2020).","guid":"RaAwIHs43TPonDvuhDR9yg","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"• Esperanza de vida más baja (60.5 años).","guid":"f5DV00TcxFa7omXfNcvDLA","children":[]}]},{"id":"36","parent":"18","text":"4. Proyecciones futuras\\N(UN, 2019):","guid":"7h_K8f9ZH8EVFHFgw6bpsg","children":[{"id":"37","parent":"36","text":"• Todas las regiones experimentarán envejecimiento.","guid":"NPoHrtDSKx48YKK6IjD_-A","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"36","text":"• Regiones menos desarrolladas → ↑ envejecimiento con mejoras socioeconómicas.","guid":"ppyi5FRRqsG1PJ8gXVwNGQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"18","text":"5. Crecimiento del n° de adultos\\Nmayores (1950-2020):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"• Regiones desarrolladas: x3 (62.7 → 246M).","guid":"EHBFm5LItB5FrMAnN24x4w","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"39","text":"• Regiones menos desarrolladas: x7 (66 → 482M).","guid":"1IXKN2WFx3UVh7RpbXCpEw","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"18","text":"6. Proyecciones\\Npara 2050:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• 15.9% de la población global ≥65 años.","guid":"GEv3PxFqLQ4QbePLQU6diw","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"• 78% en regiones menos desarrolladas.","guid":"hqr7FhuX826opELw6D9HoQ","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"• Países con mayor n° de adultos ≥65 años (2020): China, India, EE.UU.","guid":"RW-HY1X4eehRn53A5v48IQ","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"42","text":"• Japón: población más envejecida (28.4%).","guid":"gff621qX-BwFw0vGTBpkYQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"18","text":"7. Causas del envejecimiento\\N(UN, 2019):","guid":"4y_mSkh1WIwr0sYeHgW6mw","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• ↓ fertilidad.","guid":"5jTIFprH7Qa1RSpsZuvimQ","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"• ↑ esperanza de vida/↓ mortalidad.","guid":"dbd4KEBjHJ8dgml1FBk5oQ","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"47","text":"• Tasa de fertilidad (2015-2020): África Sub-Sahariana 4. 7, Oceanía (exc. Aus. y NZ) 3.5, N. África y Asia Occidental 2.9,\\NAsia Central y Meridional 2.4, A.L. y Caribe 2.0, Aus. y NZ 1.8, Asia Oriental y Sudoriental 1.8, Europa y N. América 1.7.","guid":"nTPVrUmlQnBsDKBkWJI41w","children":[]}]},{"id":"51","parent":"18","text":"8. Esperanza de vida al nacer\\N(1950-2020):","guid":"fp4n9WxLNjW3Tj76q1umGg","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"• Regiones desarrolladas: 64.8 → 79.2 años.","guid":"hV6BmRsL7OiXWg4R--0TuQ","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"51","text":"• Regiones menos desarrolladas: 41.7 → 70.7 años.","guid":"U4cvDRbnMvxhJ9QwopDs7A","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"51","text":"• Regiones más longevas (2015-2020): Japón (84.4 años), Australia y NZ (83 años).","guid":"LENlchU6RweHN5TAPgvsVg","children":[]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"18","text":"9. Migración internacional\\Ny envejecimiento:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"• Jovenes → ↓ tasa de envejecimiento en países de destino.","guid":"pQfFQ-VeX_l2um5iZ431PA","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"• Migrantes envejecen → ↑ n° de adultos mayores en países de destino.","guid":"Qp1MOsceaa5ukbJEjLFaYw","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"18","text":"10. Mujeres mayores:","guid":"XLgaqlGrSur3x9Av75fCkQ","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"• Esperanza de vida mayor que los hombres.","guid":"tweN1O49muJcxmOJ9sJVeA","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"• Mayor probabilidad de vivir solas/viudas.","guid":"JEToNt09bKLmCbPDhfdIgQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"18","text":"11. Causas de muerte\\N(OMS, 2016):","guid":"iL-ZH9pNhebf9Se8755DZg","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"• ≥70 años: 58.2% enfermedades no transmisibles, 22.6% transmisibles.","guid":"-B0-IBRzNIzsYYlzzTOGJw","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"• Principales causas: Enfermedad cardiovascular (42.1%), neoplasias malignas (15.4%).","guid":"5eHAYurrbZZwUO0xXXy5Mg","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"18","text":"12. Impacto económico:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• ↑ costos de vida/salud para adultos mayores.","guid":"2ZkBvpFOj9ZVBxLe1DUhzg","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"• Necesidad de reforma en programas sociales para sostener el envejecimiento poblacional.","guid":"RpdF-g3rsZ0aLZR0s8ST7g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"0","text":"Tendencias de Envejecimiento y\\NDemografía en EE.UU.","guid":"Lusn9Zm2PU-uc56zHs42Bg","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Proyecciones\\NPoblacionales:","guid":"FKNDMaiNG3X6W86tk8vpnQ","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"1. Envejecimiento\\Nde la población:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"• Baby boomers (1946-1964) comenzaron a cumplir 65 años en 2011.","guid":"m6Dbr2tvwq1GBahWDHb7SA","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"• 2029: El más joven cumplirá 65 años.","guid":"1E9Lp4bdIjuQwpQSkripgw","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"68","text":"2. Proporción\\Nde ≥65 años:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• 2018: 16%.","guid":"HciQSkO69PcH91hFZTevFQ","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• 2025: 18.9%.","guid":"ORf8UsW4nAC2Ab6m0mObDQ","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"• 2030: 20.6% (1 de cada 5 estadounidenses).","guid":"hGLXGLa4dBXimPQBEaZtaA","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"68","text":"3. Proporción\\Nde ≥85 años:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• 2018: 6.54M.","guid":"erLIpNpA2JtuSpAVvQIMGg","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"• 2030: 9.07M.","guid":"q-TOZE09eP8lfATETWtljg","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"• 2050: 18.56M (4.8% de la población total).","guid":"izyl4w